WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.480
If you're serious about leveling up your Python and data skills, you need to hop onto

00:00:03.480 --> 00:00:04.880
this initiative with me.

00:00:04.880 --> 00:00:08.480
Every week, Tidy Tuesday is dropping a brand new dataset and it's the perfect way to

00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:11.560
practice turning raw data into clean, insightful dashboards.

00:00:11.560 --> 00:00:14.960
Trust me, building actual projects is how you get better with Python fast.

00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:17.080
This week's dataset is all about Pixar films.

00:00:17.080 --> 00:00:20.080
I decided to turn these movie ratings into a full interactive dashboard.

00:00:20.080 --> 00:00:21.879
Here's how I built it and how you can follow along.

00:00:21.879 --> 00:00:23.000
First up is my tech stack.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:26.959
I'm using Positron as my IDE because it's designed specifically for data science workflows.

00:00:26.959 --> 00:00:29.520
I'm also building the dashboard using Quarto.

00:00:29.520 --> 00:00:33.680
It's super beginner-friendly but still powerful enough to create a polished, shareable dashboard.

00:00:33.680 --> 00:00:36.919
Then I used Pandas to clean and manipulate the dataset, handling things like merging

00:00:36.919 --> 00:00:40.480
tables, calculating averages, and reshaping data for visualizations.

00:00:40.480 --> 00:00:43.660
For the visuals, I used Plotly to create the interactive charts.

00:00:43.660 --> 00:00:46.759
By doing this, you're not just making pretty charts, you're practicing real-world data

00:00:46.759 --> 00:00:50.720
skills like data wrangling, building dynamic visualizations, structuring a project end-to-end,

00:00:50.720 --> 00:00:53.919
and you can also learn how to deploy your work so it's portfolio-ready.

00:00:53.919 --> 00:00:56.880
Leave any questions in the comments below and follow along for more data science content.

00:00:56.880 --> 00:00:57.380
Bye!

